markets.title: Will Avalanche achieve max TPS above 300 before Jan 1, 2026?
markets.rules_primary: If the maximum TPS achieved on Avalanche mainnet is above 300 before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: TPS is calculated as the maximum number of transactions processed in any one-second period or single block divided by block time, whichever methodology is standard for the specified blockchain. Measurements use the primary block explorer designated at issuance. Only mainnet transactions count; testnet activity is excluded. Layer 2s and rollups are considered separate blockchains from their Layer 1.
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the TPS threshold is definitively reached.
